# LockBox canonical toolchain pins — the ONE place tool versions live.
#
# Sourced by bump-pins.sh. Mirrored into every managed Dockerfile as `ARG` defaults
# so a plain `container build` needs no --build-arg; `./bump-pins.sh --check` (run
# by .githooks/pre-commit and `make check`) fails if the two ever diverge.
#
# SCOPE: all NINE managed devcontainers, not just this repo's two. The target list
# comes from paths.sh — the same single source sync.sh and audit.sh use — so
# onboarding a container stays a one-line edit in one file. This is the drift
# discipline paths.sh applies to the container list, applied to the toolchain:
# before this file the versions were hand-duplicated across nine Dockerfiles in
# seven repos. They all happened to agree on Node/Python, but nothing asserted it,
# and the claude pin had already split (2.1.173 in seven, 2.1.207 in two).
#
# DO NOT hand-edit the versions below. Run:
#   ./bump-pins.sh              # dry-run: what would change
#   ./bump-pins.sh --report     # pinned vs cooldown-eligible vs upstream latest
#   ./bump-pins.sh --write      # resolve + rehash + rewrite here and in both Dockerfiles
# then review the diff, `make check`, `make test`, and commit.

# --- cooldown ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Never adopt a release younger than this many days. Nearly every recent npm
# compromise (chalk/debug, nx, shai-hulud) was detected and unpublished within
# ~24h; a one-week hold costs a few days of features and removes essentially all
# of the zero-day-publish exposure. Lower this only with a stated reason.
COOLDOWN_DAYS=7

# --- Claude Code ------------------------------------------------------------
# The npm package is a ~20 KB WRAPPER; the real executable ships in a per-arch
# optionalDependency (@anthropic-ai/claude-code-linux-{arm64,x64}) that the
# wrapper's postinstall copies over bin/claude.exe. So the version alone pins
# nothing meaningful — the SHA-256s below are of the actual native binary, and
# each Dockerfile asserts the installed binary matches before the build proceeds.
# Regenerate with bump-pins.sh; never transcribe by hand.
CLAUDE_CODE_VERSION=2.1.207
CLAUDE_CODE_SHA256_ARM64=8bc14a284065383460f37981d724b8f7aa7ca93c9849d2fe367e08f03383f454
CLAUDE_CODE_SHA256_AMD64=85e7e988a392d859f90802ca21fb26e89d3c9ab527f5ed0b08df3955e34d5c83

# --- safe-chain (Aikido supply-chain screening) -----------------------------
# Baked into the image (root prefix), NOT installed at runtime. NOTE: unlike
# claude, its 8 transitive deps resolve from the registry at build time and are
# not hash-pinned — this is a version pin with review, not a closure pin.
SAFE_CHAIN_VERSION=1.5.12

# --- Node.js ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Self-verifying: the Dockerfiles download nodejs.org's SHASUMS256.txt for this
# exact version and `sha256sum -c` the tarball, so no separate hash is needed here.
NODE_VERSION=24.15.0

# --- Python (python-build-standalone) ---------------------------------------
# Self-verifying the same way, against the release's SHA256SUMS asset.
PY_RELEASE=20260510
PY_VERSION=3.12.13

# --- Not pinned here --------------------------------------------------------
# gh + the apt packages are deliberately unpinned: Debian/cli.github.com drop old
# versions from their mirrors, so a hard pin breaks cache-miss rebuilds outright.
# Integrity for those comes from the launch-time verify-pins gate instead, which
# fingerprints gh/git alongside the pinned tools and fails closed on drift.
